Text: Hey, that's...
Huh? Is that...!
Annerose of Velgalta's Seven Blades.

Oh yeah, the one who beat an ancient warrior at the
Goddess' Trial a while back.
Man, talk about an imposing aura...
Hm?!
You there.
Huh?
Cid turns around to see a young dark knight.

(My heart leaps in my chest. No way... Is this really
happening...?!)
Are you planning to enter the Bushin Festival?

Your sword is cheap, and your body is frail. Nothing
redeemable in the slightest.

(Yep, called it... The scene that happens without
fail when the wimpy guy tries to enter the big
tourney.)

Annerose walks over to me, stopping about an arm's
length away. She has fierce, light blue eyes and her
shoulder-length hair is the same color

She gives me a stern once-over. In my head, I flex
and show off my stuff.
I'm telling you this for your own good.
Don't enter the Bushin Festival.

Take this lightly, and you'll be lucky if you can
walk away in one piece.
*sigh*
Huh?
Don't judge people by their looks.
What? I'm trying to look out for you...
Save it.
(I purposefully choose a bold way of speaking.)
Hey, I'm not done talking to you...
(Going with this look was a good call.)

(Can't believe I pulled off the perfect "looks weak
but is actually a shadowbroker" move so soon!)
Not so fast, big fella.
When someone's tryin' to help, it pays to listen.

(Wuh-oh, say hello to your stereotypical cannon
fodder!)
(I'd describe his look as "brutish pro wrestler.")

(But the big, well-worn sword at his waist and the
scars across his face also give him the air of a dude
who's seen his fair share of battles.)

(Truth is, he's probably the strongest person here
after me and Annerose.)
Yeah, I just said that...
The name's Quinton.

I've fought in the festival plenty of times, and
there's always chumps like you ruining the mood.
So c'mon, scoot your little ass on home to Mommy.
Hahahaha! You tell 'em!
Oh man...
What was that?
(I gotta do it.)
I'm stronger than you at least.
(I gotta ride the big wave!)
Grr...!
He's givin' ya lip, Quinton!
You just gonna take that?

Quinton glowers at the jeers and grabs me by the
collar.
You think can take me?
You better watch that mouth of yours!
He sends me flying with a punch as he speaks.
You wanna apologize, better do it now.
You really are a loser.
Grrrrrr...
You're dead!

(Quinton's charging me with fists swinging like a
complete amateur.)

(Frankly speaking, this world is really behind the
times when it comes to unarmed combat.)
(I have plenty of viable options in this situation.)

(If there was a tourney for barefisted gorillas, er,
humans, I'd have it in the bag, no problem.)

(In a real fight against someone I need to worry
about, I'd go for the eyes first.)

(I don't intend to get down and dirty just yet,
though.)
Oraaa!!!
I ain't through with you yet, punk!
(Quinton's fists batter away at me.)
(Left, right, left, right, right, right.)

(I let him hammer on me for a bit without even
lifting a finger before crumpling when the timing is
right.)
C'mon, man, at least try to fight back.
He's as weak as he looks.
(The ridicule of the crowd feels good.)
Aww, too scared to hit me?
My fists are too good for the likes of you.
Looks like somebody hasn't learned their lesson.
I think this has gone far enough.
What'd you say...?
If you want to continue, you'll have to face me.
...Tch.
Wassamatter, Quinton? Piss yer pants?
Damn, just when it was gettin' good.
Wanna say that again?!
Quinton leaves, as do the ring of onlookers.
You okay?
I'm sorry. I didn't expect things to go that far.

But you could've stopped him whenever you wanted.
Am I wrong?

Since you could be facing irreparable damage in the
festival, I thought a little dose of pain here would
do you some good.
Anyway, you should get those cuts
No need.
Huh?
It's been awhile since I tasted blood.
Uh...
*gasp*

(Looks like she noticed I didn't take any obvious
damage despite the pounding I took.)
After all that, you aren't even...?!
It's really been awhile...since I tasted blood.
Wait!
I can feel her staring intently at my back.
I'm Annerose Nichtsehen.
And you are?
Mundane. Mundane Mann.
Mundane Mann...
I melt into the crowd.
The line to sign up is over here.
Stay out of the roadway, please!

You there! Keep your sword in its sheath, or we'll
turn you over to the knights!
(Hell yeah! I actually pulled it off...)

(Everybody thinks I'm just some lowly chump...except
for a few people who sense there's something
different about me!)
(I got a pretty good reaction outta that girl.)

But let's not get too excited yet... The main act is
yet to come.

The best play here would be to give 'em hints of my
strength once the tournament starts.

And then once the climax rolls around, I'll blow 'em
all away with how powerful I am!
In order to do that, I'll need to...
Next, Mundane Mann!
Uh, that'd be me.

I've already completed my registration for the
festival in preparation for that fateful moment.
